deliverables.change:
Delete the shadowOnly block entirely. unified becomes just enriched.

Remove:
  const shadowOnly = shadowRecs
    .filter(r => r.action !== 'NO_TRADE' && !r.resolved)
    .filter(r => !openTrades.some(t => t.market_slug === r.market_slug))
    .map(r => ({ ...r, _type: 'shadow', _source: 'shadow' }));

  const unified = [...enriched, ...shadowOnly];
  $('pos-count').textContent = enriched.length + shadowOnly.length;

Replace with:
  const unified = enriched;
  $('pos-count').textContent = enriched.length;

Do NOT remove fetchShadow(), renderShadow(), renderShadowFeed(), or the Shadow tab. Shadow data is still fetched, still used for enrichment, and still rendered in the Shadow drawer tab. Only the shadowOnly card injection into the Positions panel is removed.

The current line:
  const unrlzdUsd = r.unrealized_pnl_dollars ?? r.pnl_usd ?? null;

For paper positions (_type='paper'), r.unrealized_pnl_dollars comes from shadow's fixed-size estimate ($50). But the real paper trade has r.qty (actual contracts) and r.entry_px and r.current_price. Recompute for paper positions:

  let unrlzdUsd;
  if (r._type === 'paper' && r.qty != null && r.entry_px != null && r.current_price != null) {
    const isBuyYes = (r.side || r.action) === 'BUY_YES';
    unrlzdUsd = isBuyYes
      ? (r.current_price - r.entry_px) * r.qty
      : (r.entry_px - r.current_price) * r.qty;
    unrlzdUsd = Math.round(unrlzdUsd * 100) / 100;
  } else {
    unrlzdUsd = r.unrealized_pnl_dollars ?? r.pnl_usd ?? null;
  }

Note: r.current_price on an enriched paper position comes from the shadow rec merge (it is ask_yes or ask_no from the shadow log). If no shadow rec matched, current_price will be null and unrlzdUsd will fall through to pnl_usd (which is null for open trades — shows '—'). This is correct behavior.

After the enriched block is computed, bind the open count from enriched.length (real paper positions) rather than letting renderState() set kpi-open from state.open_positions (which can lag behind DB by one state.json write cycle).

Add at the end of renderUnifiedPositions(), before or after the innerHTML assignment:
  $('kpi-open').textContent = enriched.length;
  $('cmd-open').textContent = enriched.length;

This makes pos-count, kpi-open, and cmd-open all show the same number: the count of real open paper trades. renderState() still sets kpi-open from state initially, but renderUnifiedPositions() (called after every fetchShadow and fetchTrades) will keep it anchored to the DB truth.
